WEBVTT

00:01.441 --> 00:02.761
<i>With all the bureaucracy
in the hospital,</i>

00:02.762 --> 00:05.370
<i>sometimes you have to bend
the rules to help a patient.</i>

00:05.371 --> 00:07.776
<i>Unfortunately, the new
Chief of Medicine didn't like it</i>

00:07.876 --> 00:09.211
<i>and she was everywhere.</i>

00:09.464 --> 00:10.784
<i>Patient rooms--</i>

00:10.785 --> 00:12.312
What you doing, rockstar?

00:12.331 --> 00:13.390
Uh, nothing, I'm just, uh...

00:14.374 --> 00:17.690
[ Song: Lookin' Over My Shoulder
Band: The Basics ]

00:18.682 --> 00:19.724
That's not right!

00:19.725 --> 00:21.148
<i>Work stations...</i>

00:21.721 --> 00:23.510
You need to wear a bell.

00:24.135 --> 00:25.692
<i>Even the O.R!</i>

00:25.693 --> 00:27.655
Thanks for letting
me observe, fellas.

00:27.689 --> 00:30.259
Come on,
you got five more surgeries today!

00:30.971 --> 00:32.873
Tumour's down by his bean bags!

00:33.345 --> 00:35.360
We should probably take that out.

00:35.838 --> 00:38.339
It's like, all of a sudden,
this hospital is a police state.

00:38.356 --> 00:39.158
I mean,
next thing you know,

00:39.218 --> 00:41.126
they're gonna be charging doctors
for candy at the gift shop.

00:41.274 --> 00:43.875
They do charge doctors for
candy at the gift shop, Elliot.

00:43.892 --> 00:44.760
Really?

00:44.917 --> 00:47.035
Then, why does Johann always let me--

00:47.036 --> 00:50.265
Because he wants to make you his
wife and bring you back to Estonia.

00:51.568 --> 00:53.901
That's why he's always asking me
if I'm comfortable around oxen.

00:54.000 --> 00:55.384
Elliot, I'm trying to
talk to you about Maddox

00:55.434 --> 00:57.032
and how we can't work the system anymore.

00:57.417 --> 00:58.459
Correction:

00:58.615 --> 01:00.681
You can't work the system anymore.

01:00.716 --> 01:02.522
I, can.

01:02.731 --> 01:05.596
For instance, I just got Mr. Tillman
back there into a clinical trial

01:05.597 --> 01:08.965
that has a cut-off age of 30.
He's actually 35.

01:08.973 --> 01:11.873
But if anyone asks Mr. Tillman,
you're how old?

01:11.958 --> 01:13.109
35!

01:13.503 --> 01:15.014
I forgot to mention

01:15.049 --> 01:17.280
that it is a clinical
trial for head injuries.

01:17.575 --> 01:19.034
- Ah, he hurt his head.
- Ah!

01:19.225 --> 01:20.649
The point is,

01:20.753 --> 01:24.053
that I'm still able to give
top-notch care to my patients,

01:24.132 --> 01:25.954
whereas you, are not.

01:26.180 --> 01:27.673
35!

01:28.326 --> 01:29.854
You know why?

01:30.045 --> 01:32.876
I am a much, much
better doctor than you.

01:35.183 --> 01:37.968
Ooh, look at that big lollipop!

01:38.055 --> 01:39.811
I wouldn't know whether I'll lick it

01:39.891 --> 01:43.053
or that it'd just lift up my
skirt and spank myself with it.

01:43.551 --> 01:44.436
Elliot!

01:44.507 --> 01:45.584
It's free candy!

01:46.759 --> 01:50.614
Dr. Reid, I thought you gave a great
endocrynology lecture today,

01:50.718 --> 01:54.582
even though some of the other interns think
you go of on personal tangents too much.

01:54.652 --> 01:55.503
Who?

01:55.520 --> 01:57.234
Oh, I shouldn't say.

01:57.410 --> 01:58.088
Denise.

01:58.122 --> 01:58.817
Anyway, I was hoping

01:58.834 --> 02:01.348
you could have signed me some
more interesting procedures?

02:01.383 --> 02:02.351
Rain it in...

02:02.420 --> 02:03.080
Katie.

02:03.184 --> 02:05.303
Just go place a
central line on Mr. Clark.

02:05.373 --> 02:06.349
Thanks!

02:06.384 --> 02:07.461
Wow!

02:07.365 --> 02:09.332
The butt-kissing isn't even the worst part.

02:09.401 --> 02:11.780
I feel like Katie will do
anything to get ahead, you know.

02:11.815 --> 02:13.778
I'm this close to
freezing her olive (sp?).

02:14.229 --> 02:16.126
Just like I did Dr. Simmons.

02:16.143 --> 02:18.047
Yeah,
what would you do with her?

02:18.091 --> 02:21.391
Hello, she wears the exact
same thing as me everyday.

02:21.478 --> 02:22.120
Yeah,

02:22.155 --> 02:23.996
we're talking about you, skank!

02:24.187 --> 02:25.775
Nice dress!

02:26.192 --> 02:29.752
Veronica, I have no idea how are
you doing this! But I will find out.

02:31.780 --> 02:32.787
35!

02:33.187 --> 02:34.402
Hi, Mr. Tillman.

02:34.663 --> 02:36.243
You ready to go to work?

02:37.300 --> 02:38.690
Hello, Mr. Rosell!

02:38.742 --> 02:40.079
You can call me Pat.

02:40.096 --> 02:41.902
This is my daughter Christine.

02:41.944 --> 02:44.080
So Pat, I understand that you
have multiple sclerosis

02:44.115 --> 02:46.373
and that you are interested
being put on Interferon.

02:46.390 --> 02:48.318
I held off
as long as I could but,

02:48.352 --> 02:51.687
now the hand spasms and
the nausea are pretty bad.

02:51.739 --> 02:53.146
Plus, I'm colour-blind.

02:53.284 --> 02:55.542
Well, we're gonna go run
a whole bunch of tests.

02:55.785 --> 02:57.299
<i>And get some coffee.</i>

02:58.259 --> 02:58.990
Oh!

02:59.771 --> 03:01.247
Dammit!

03:01.351 --> 03:02.654
Now I have to go change.

03:03.592 --> 03:04.651
So,

03:04.721 --> 03:05.849
how you holding up?

03:05.868 --> 03:08.959
Cleaning's an art,
my mop was my paintbrush.

03:09.307 --> 03:12.450
<i>Oh no, it's the first time I've
seen the janitor since he was fired.</i>

03:12.519 --> 03:14.169
<i>I have to seem like I care.</i>

03:14.221 --> 03:15.784
<i>Think of the saddest thing you can.</i>

03:16.226 --> 03:19.613
<i>Turk's dead, Turk's dead,
Turk's dead, Turk's de--</i>

03:19.907 --> 03:21.123
<i>Oh my God!</i>

03:21.453 --> 03:22.572
<i>What if something
really happened to him?</i>

03:22.682 --> 03:23.476
<i>I'd be lost!</i>

03:23.753 --> 03:25.716
<i>Stop thinking like that,
Turk's fine!</i>

03:25.837 --> 03:27.886
<i>Turk's fine, Turk's fine,
Turk's fine, Turk's fine!</i>

03:27.956 --> 03:29.171
JD!

03:29.675 --> 03:31.134
The janitor got fired.

03:31.168 --> 03:32.673
No, it's okay.

03:32.778 --> 03:34.896
He knows,
he just doesn't care.

03:35.053 --> 03:37.441
See, in his mind, I'm the
bad guy in our relationship,

03:37.475 --> 03:39.526
even though if he stopped to think
about it for a minute, he would realise

03:39.607 --> 03:41.634
I never did a thing to
him that he didn't deserve.

03:41.817 --> 03:43.910
You locked me in a water tower!

03:43.944 --> 03:45.177
You were on the wall.

03:45.229 --> 03:47.140
You destroyed my scooter, Sasha!

03:47.174 --> 03:48.675
You know I hate Wednesdays.

03:48.721 --> 03:50.753
You haunted my pediatric patients.

03:50.805 --> 03:53.462
You didn't wear the shorts that
my imaginary wife made for you.

03:53.514 --> 03:56.152
Janitor, I just heard.
I'm so sorry!

03:56.725 --> 03:57.750
What?

03:58.670 --> 04:00.052
'Sup?

04:00.226 --> 04:02.640
Oh, come on!
How's that even possible?

04:06.004 --> 04:09.041
'My Saving Grace'

04:12.528 --> 04:13.939
VO Transcript And Edits By: VeRdiKT

04:14.005 --> 04:15.245
For SubScene.com
