04:18.161 --> 04:19.151
35!

04:20.790 --> 04:21.281
Hey!

04:21.315 --> 04:23.667
Thanks for placing that
central line for me.

04:23.875 --> 04:26.498
I'm just so not great at
that procedure, you know.

04:26.741 --> 04:28.157
Look at you,

04:28.309 --> 04:32.598
watching over the ICU like a proud
lioness looking out over her jungle.

04:32.599 --> 04:34.282
Elliot, stop.

04:34.803 --> 04:36.394
Oh my God,
that wasn't a real 'stop',

04:36.395 --> 04:39.503
that was a 'keep going because
I'm actually loving this stop', wasn't it?

04:40.273 --> 04:41.211
Maybe...

04:42.149 --> 04:44.549
I never got one of these before!
This is so exciting!

04:44.584 --> 04:46.321
I'll leave before I ruin it.

04:49.401 --> 04:51.312
Great job on
Mr. Clark's central line.

04:51.364 --> 04:53.170
Thanks, it was super easy.

04:56.923 --> 04:59.771
Okay Mr. Rosell,
let's get you on in some Interferon.

04:59.858 --> 05:03.748
So it can start interferring
with that pesky MS of yours.

05:03.902 --> 05:06.142
Are you making fun
of my multiple sclerosis?

05:06.194 --> 05:06.941
Sorry, I mean...

05:06.975 --> 05:10.258
I'm just trying to lighten the moment.
It won't happen again, I promise.

05:10.431 --> 05:14.286
<i>Interferon, sounds like the name of
a robot that always gets in the way.</i>

05:14.380 --> 05:16.603
So we brought you some pills
for your pain and your nausea.

05:16.655 --> 05:17.940
Dr. Dorian?

05:19.407 --> 05:21.439
- JD. Pills.
- Right, pills.

05:21.500 --> 05:23.618
Take the red one now
for the pain.

05:26.447 --> 05:28.375
Mr. Rosell took the red pill.

05:28.531 --> 05:29.816
Yeah, we told him to.

05:29.851 --> 05:33.151
If he can't see colours,
how did he know which one is red?

05:33.785 --> 05:36.858
He's just another addict
scamming us for meds.

05:37.431 --> 05:39.081
Frick on a stick!

05:42.417 --> 05:44.240
Looking for something?

05:44.397 --> 05:46.324
Yes, my 'Cloak of Invisibility',

05:46.393 --> 05:50.231
so that I can avoid conversations with
soul-less dictators such as yourself.

05:50.300 --> 05:52.254
Unfortunately,
it's really hard to find,

05:52.306 --> 05:54.407
because as the name suggests,

05:54.494 --> 05:55.901
it's invisible.

05:56.109 --> 05:58.013
Alright, Dr. Cox.

05:58.117 --> 05:59.402
Ridiculous name,
by the way.

05:59.958 --> 06:02.030
If you're looking for your patient
Mr. Tillman,

06:02.100 --> 06:05.868
my guess is he's probably in a
bus somewhere, screaming, "35!".

06:06.094 --> 06:07.787
See, I've anounced him
from his head trauma trial

06:07.788 --> 06:11.434
because I learned that
somebody was lying about his age.

06:12.381 --> 06:13.214
See ya!

06:15.759 --> 06:19.423
I gotta get rid of this Maddox.
Honest to God, she is...

06:19.597 --> 06:21.333
Why aren't you listening to me?

06:21.439 --> 06:22.985
Because of that.

06:24.079 --> 06:26.076
That scone looks good.

06:26.117 --> 06:27.194
Oh yeah?

06:32.000 --> 06:34.292
We should have sex later.

06:34.362 --> 06:37.296
How did you get from
that image to that thought?

06:37.887 --> 06:39.491
I'll tell you tonight.

06:39.514 --> 06:42.518
Just bring home a scone
and a Hawaiian shirt.

06:42.872 --> 06:45.169
Mama's heating up!

06:45.870 --> 06:46.894
Donnie,

06:46.947 --> 06:49.482
do my free muffins per
wife include scones?

06:49.517 --> 06:50.489
Nope.

06:50.559 --> 06:51.742
Damn you, God!

06:54.000 --> 06:56.320
I am getting rid of Maddox.
Who's in?

06:56.355 --> 06:57.497
I'm in.

06:57.792 --> 06:59.852
Ever since you fired me,
I've been moping around my apartment,

06:59.952 --> 07:01.014
making parking sounds.

07:01.960 --> 07:03.419
I-I'm not crazy,

07:03.462 --> 07:04.981
I just need some human interaction

07:05.016 --> 07:08.107
and the barking makes the neighbours yell,
"Shut the damn thing up!"

07:08.298 --> 07:11.154
Then I can go over there with a bottle
of scotch and apologize for Rusty,

07:11.172 --> 07:12.717
my imaginary akita.

07:13.212 --> 07:15.487
The only downside is that about
the time Lady, my girlfriend,

07:15.522 --> 07:17.727
gets home,
I'm too drunk to talk to her.

07:17.814 --> 07:19.290
Much less make love.

07:20.384 --> 07:23.093
You've never pictured me as an
organism that has sex, have you?

07:23.117 --> 07:24.854
- We have not.
- No.

07:24.923 --> 07:25.757
I understand.

07:25.774 --> 07:28.448
Is Dr. Maddox really that bad?

07:28.483 --> 07:31.183
Hmm, she's like you.
Only smarter on the ball.

07:31.340 --> 07:32.712
That must suck!

07:34.651 --> 07:35.398
Admit it.

07:35.797 --> 07:39.618
You miss having me as the
Chief of Medicine.

07:40.226 --> 07:41.242
Bob!

07:41.276 --> 07:43.895
I will gladly admit to
anything that's true,

07:44.046 --> 07:45.202
no matter how embarrasing.

07:45.548 --> 07:46.494
For example,

07:46.546 --> 07:49.575
I've always wished that I
could carry a child inside of me,

07:49.575 --> 07:51.190
and you know, birth it.

07:51.382 --> 07:54.369
But I'll never admit
to missing you, Bob.

07:54.690 --> 07:55.506
Ever.

07:55.558 --> 07:56.808
Rusty, heel!

07:59.613 --> 08:00.831
Donnie,

08:00.970 --> 08:05.138
I'm gonna need a Double Chocolate
Blaster as a 'pick-me-up'.

08:06.901 --> 08:08.290
Maybe another.

08:10.921 --> 08:12.588
Hello, girls.

08:13.628 --> 08:15.363
Oh, sit down, Katie,
sit down!

08:15.364 --> 08:17.295
It's time to set you straight!

08:17.296 --> 08:20.418
But we'd better do it fast because,
man, you're annoying.

08:20.423 --> 08:23.027
Why do you think you
can talk to me like this?

08:23.045 --> 08:24.573
You're just a nurse.

08:25.042 --> 08:25.858
Okay.

08:25.893 --> 08:26.622
A:

08:26.665 --> 08:28.193
I'm a lioness.

08:28.367 --> 08:29.096
B:

08:29.287 --> 08:32.066
Who the hell do you think
runs this place?

08:32.265 --> 08:34.765
The nursing staff is
already turned on you.

08:34.878 --> 08:38.698
Why do you think you were assigned
75 baldous impactions (sp?) this week?

08:38.828 --> 08:40.835
I don't care, I'm good at it.

08:41.059 --> 08:42.988
Plus, this morning,
I found a silver dollar.

08:43.596 --> 08:45.940
Everyone's onto you,
missy.

08:46.392 --> 08:48.302
Pretty soon,
you're gonna get called out.

08:49.062 --> 08:50.399
You're lying to us.

08:50.469 --> 08:52.518
You took the red pill,
you can see colours.

08:52.665 --> 08:55.496
You know, I'm
sick and tired of low-lifes like you

08:55.530 --> 08:58.907
trying to come here and
squirt pain medication off of us, okay?

08:58.959 --> 09:00.418
You make us care

09:00.435 --> 09:02.867
and then because you're word,
we're gonna see through your little plan.

09:02.901 --> 09:04.551
You don't even laugh
at our jokes.

09:04.690 --> 09:07.538
Actually, the Interferon joke
was sort of funny.

09:07.573 --> 09:09.776
You damn right it was, Pat!
Okay?

09:09.811 --> 09:11.548
But this time,
no one's getting off easy.

09:11.565 --> 09:13.076
My cousin is a cop.

09:13.249 --> 09:14.569
And not a good cop either,

09:14.604 --> 09:15.767
a rogue cop!

09:16.375 --> 09:18.265
- Christine, it's you, isn't it?
- Hold on, hold on Elliot.

09:18.266 --> 09:20.107
You ever watched The Shield, Pat?

09:20.125 --> 09:22.035
Do you happen to get FX, Pat?

09:22.044 --> 09:23.902
Because you're gonna get
Michael Chicklest!

09:23.919 --> 09:24.666
In the head!

09:24.770 --> 09:27.096
He's the orange guy
in Fantastic Four;

09:27.097 --> 09:28.399
that's coming down on ya!

09:28.434 --> 09:29.250
JD!

09:29.667 --> 09:32.037
Look at her hand,
it's in spasm.

09:32.124 --> 09:34.590
You're the one who
wants the MS, right?

09:35.693 --> 09:38.583
I don't have any insurance and
my dad just thought that since he did--

09:38.584 --> 09:40.563
Look, we'll go, alright?

09:40.589 --> 09:43.176
If you, uh,
could just not tell anyone,

09:43.298 --> 09:44.922
we'd be very grateful.

09:45.529 --> 09:47.946
<i>Elliot and I knew
what we had to do.</i>

09:48.137 --> 09:49.509
Okay, Pat.

09:49.630 --> 09:50.776
You have MS.

09:51.809 --> 09:54.839
And you're not leaving here
until you get your medication.

09:56.437 --> 09:57.479
Thank you.

09:57.760 --> 10:00.070
Do you know how grateful
people would be

10:00.139 --> 10:03.525
if you showed them even
a little common decency.

10:03.682 --> 10:06.373
Oh please!
This place is so competitive.

10:06.790 --> 10:08.874
No one looks out
for each other here.

10:09.386 --> 10:12.076
Ah, yeah.
This Maddox is a damn sketchy.

10:12.196 --> 10:14.643
I guarantee you will find
something in these files.

10:15.188 --> 10:17.228
Hurry up, man,
I don't wanna get busted!

10:17.541 --> 10:20.215
Now listen there, great babe,
I only invited you to help me

10:20.224 --> 10:22.082
because it had never dawned
on me that you'd get all

10:22.099 --> 10:24.374
panicky over a little
breaking-and-entering.

10:24.426 --> 10:25.520
Actually, I'm not.

10:25.537 --> 10:27.430
See, this stuff has
become so mundane to me

10:27.448 --> 10:28.924
that I've created a character

10:28.959 --> 10:30.487
who's terrified about
going back to prison.

10:30.504 --> 10:31.477
And through him,

10:31.512 --> 10:34.412
I hope to feel once again,
the old rush.

10:34.724 --> 10:35.957
You carry on.

10:36.054 --> 10:36.870
Good.

10:36.905 --> 10:39.058
'Cause I can't go back there, man!

10:39.076 --> 10:41.038
Not after what they did to Johnny!

10:41.281 --> 10:44.016
Oh Johnny, he was the best.
I wish you knew him.

10:46.099 --> 10:48.009
They shaked him with a shiv,

10:48.547 --> 10:50.388
then they shift him with a shick.

10:51.160 --> 10:53.140
Out for a pack of smokes.

10:53.305 --> 10:54.520
Johnny,

10:54.642 --> 10:57.316
you were too beautiful
for this world, man.

10:57.828 --> 10:59.790
I'll be king in the next!

11:01.944 --> 11:03.489
Johnny!

11:03.819 --> 11:05.295
Johnny.

11:07.969 --> 11:09.515
Hey, guys?

11:09.550 --> 11:10.192
Listen!

11:10.229 --> 11:13.058
I popped in here earlier
and not Mr. Rosell

11:13.075 --> 11:15.046
but his daughter showing signs of MS.

11:15.098 --> 11:18.606
They were lying to get her the drugs.
Can you believe it?

11:18.649 --> 11:19.604
I'm angry!

11:19.605 --> 11:21.758
I wanna shake these things!

11:21.775 --> 11:22.506
Hard!

11:22.524 --> 11:25.823
Anyway, I played the bad guy for you
and I tossed them out.

11:25.962 --> 11:27.872
I love playing the bad guy!

11:27.916 --> 11:30.208
I'd even wear black scrubs
if they made them.

11:31.632 --> 11:34.324
Do you even know what people
are calling you around here?

11:34.636 --> 11:36.147
I know, I don't care.

11:36.165 --> 11:38.961
Because I wrote the worst one
on this piece of paper.

11:41.670 --> 11:44.691
Sausages, sausages
and more sausages?

11:44.726 --> 11:46.254
It's actually...

11:46.280 --> 11:48.052
Turk's grocery list.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.101
But you do care,
don't you?

11:50.465 --> 11:52.566
Katie, if you keep
going down this road,

11:52.583 --> 11:55.240
eventually,
people will come after you.

11:55.570 --> 11:56.612
Hey, you!

11:56.690 --> 11:58.895
How do you think the board will feel
if I can show 'em proof that

11:58.896 --> 12:01.935
you're in the take
for a medical supply company?

12:02.043 --> 12:03.484
I'm guessing they'd be thrilled

12:03.519 --> 12:06.523
since I'm rolling that money
back into the hospital's budget.

12:06.714 --> 12:09.250
Please,
stop handcuffing us!

12:09.328 --> 12:13.201
You're making it impossible
for us to help our patients.

12:14.677 --> 12:17.471
Does anybody else
feel that way?

12:20.540 --> 12:21.842
Great!

12:21.912 --> 12:24.794
Now I don't have to tell you
each individually that, um...

12:24.820 --> 12:27.599
I don't give a rat's hairy ass!

12:28.562 --> 12:30.646
It's a huge time-saver!

12:31.054 --> 12:32.287
Thanks, gang!

12:32.395 --> 12:34.166
And eventually, Katie,

12:34.218 --> 12:36.511
everyone here is
gonna hate you.

12:39.368 --> 12:40.976
Look, Carla,

12:41.063 --> 12:43.199
I appreciate this whole
mother-hen thing...

12:43.234 --> 12:43.946
Lioness.

12:43.980 --> 12:47.923
Lioness thing that you've got going
on here, but I don't need your help.

12:47.981 --> 12:50.274
Look, I know you think
you're fine on your own,

